or=d1c3b5 class=headings><font color=#000000>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usongmistressjenelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Songmistress Jenelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Song Mistress</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/22/01 2:56:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Guilds?</span><hr size=1> I hate to agree with the resident Grumpy Gus (*teases Kal*) but he's right.  It doesn't show a lot of organization and planning when you /auction WTB GUILD MEMBERS SEND TELLS!  That actually shows a LACK of organization.  So you don't know ten people who are going to be on at once - fine.  Wait a few weeks, get to know more people... have your friends list expand.  Then things will be SO much easier. <br>
<br>
I can not imagine leading a guild and inviting people I don't know.  Honestly, I would have to know EVERY person that joined before I could approve of them.  How do you know that the person you just invited isn't going to be a ninja looter, or a d00d, or a l00t whore, or someone as vile as Ankles?  I mean, come on.  That cute little half elf could be the EVIL MUD SLINGING BOARD ADMIN OF DOOM.  Do you want a person like *that* in your guild?  I know I don't!<br>
<br>
Of course, guilds that teeter on a weak foundation won't last.<br>
<br>
Which is why I'm encouraging you all to join MY guild.  Gotta catch 'em all!  &lt;Pokemon&gt;<br>
<br>
Back on a serious note, even if this is a roleplaying server, you should try and have your guild promote honor and respect among its members and the server population.  I would never join a guild with a reputation for being mean or nasty.  Nor would I stay in one that developed said reputation due to an actual chain of events.  Other people aren't like that.  And that's fine with me. <br>
<br>
Jenelle<br>
Song Mistress of Firiona Vie<br>
1st Fist of Light<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulorddenman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lord Denman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/22/01 3:07:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Guilds?</span><hr size=1> With all due respect to Bane (with whom I agree on many other points), I believe the way guilds are set up now are adequate.  VI engages in guild wipes every so often so the weaker guilds at that time don't exist anymore.  Poorly organized guilds fold up shop for lack of interest/participation anyway.<br>
<br>
On E'ci, I started out in one guild, and when leadership issues arose, moved to a successor guild.  I'm still on good terms with the remaining members of the original guild, although I don't see them as often as I used to.  <br>
<br>
The successor guild continues to grow, although we have the usual growth issues:  we need more members who are of this class in order to raid better vs. we need to keep this a guild among friends, not strangers.  The successor guild is basically open to anyone -- although they have to group with our guildmembers for a sufficient amount of time to develop an appreciation of their behavior/personality.<br>
<br>
In any event, forming guilds should not be too difficult.  The hard part will be keeping them together, as anyone who has been in one will attest.<br>
<br>
Maedhros<br>
Druid, 3rd Circle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubanegrivm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Banegrivm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 253<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/22/01 3:23:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=17>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Guilds?</span><hr size=1> Yes Mae your right, but...why should it go on? I mean basicly all VI is doing in a sense is spinning its wheels and making more work for themselves. If they had a more selective guild procedure it would make the whole overall program operate more efficiently and effect game play in a positive manner. Imagine if for once you could go to a guild leader to solve a problem instead of using a petition and they HAD to answer it because of complaints started rolling in against their guild it meant THEY were the ones coming under the gun. I.E. they become held accountable and responsible for their actions of their membership. It would save CS a ton of hassles I think in the grand retrospect, you also wouldn't see 500 guild on a server and the guilds that did exist would have character and depth to them. Rich and full of vibrant life. <p>Banegrivm Shadowblight<br>Sovereign Lord of the 1st Fist of Light<br>www.1stfistoflight.com</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubanegrivm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Banegrivm</A> at: 10/22/01 3:25:47 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uanklesdirtyfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ankles Dirtyfoot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mudslingin' Admin</span><br>  Posts: 225<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/22/01 3:53:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Guilds?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
...or someone as vile as Ankles? I mean, come on. That cute little half elf could be the EVIL MUD SLINGING BOARD ADMIN OF DOOM. Do you want a person like *that* in your guild? I know I don't!<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
